msContents.summary: This manuscript is a book of hours, Use of Paris (except for the hymn in Prime). Most of the manuscript was made in France in the late fifteenth century. It is lacking a calendar, and six of the fifteen large illuminations marking major text divisions are now missing. The fifteenth-century manuscript is written in Latin, except for two prayers at the end in Middle French (fols. 141r-148r), and decorated with illuminated side borders and letters on every page. Additional prayers in French (including a prayer to Saint Michael, a prayer to a guardian angel, a prayer for one's enemies, and prayers to the Virgin) and Latin (including prayers to Saint Barbara, Saint Appollonia, Saints Cosmas and Damian, and the Virgin, as well as a litany of the angels), written in a humanist hand probably in the sixteenth century, have been added on the final blank parchment leaf (fol. 149) and added paper leaves at the end (fols. 150-177).

supportDesc.extent: i+177+i; 185 x 138 mm bound to 191 x 146 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto

layoutDesc.layout: One column of fourteen lines, frame-ruled in red ink (fols. 1r- 149v); one column of fourteen to nineteen lines, crudely frame-ruled in red or brown ink (possibly after the text was written, fols. 150r-177v); written area: 97 x 62 mm (fols. 1r-149v), 118-122 x 77-81 mm (fols. 150r-177v)

decoDesc.decoNote: Nine large arched miniatures (Evangelist portrait of John, fol. 1r; Nativity, fol. 37r; Annunciation to the Shepherds, fol. 43v; Presentation in the Temple, fol. 52v; Flight into Egypt, fol. 57v; King David in prayer, fol. 71r; Pentecost, fol. 99r; a burial scene, fol. 106r; and the Trinity, fol. 144r), with full borders of ivy leaves, flowers, berries, and acanthus leaves, and illuminated letters on gold grounds; outer borders of ivy leaves, flowers, berries, and acanthus leaves throughout; illuminated initials, one or two lines in height, in gold on blue and pink grounds throughout; blue, pink, and gold line fillers throughout; rubrication in red; occasional early modern floral decorations in borders of later paper leaves (fols. 151r, 155v, 160r)
144rLarge illumination, The Trinity with Christ crucified

binding.p: Seventeenth- or eighteenth-century leather (?), gilt-tooled; marbled paper pastedowns; joints cracked
